column14: -RiverRay Measurement, tethered boat off manned boat -Measurement plots unexpectetly far off curve -Techs switched positions after first two transects and completed two more transects with the same results. -Techs re-did levels to ensure that was not the source of error. -Both techs reviewed measurement multiple times and could not find anything incorrect -Therefore it must be assumed that the shift is correct. -May be due to high water this spring? but this does not explain why measurement earlier this summer plotted ~3% off the curve only. @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ 0.748m offset after reset ADCP by Moving Boat
